{"title":"Qx Aneurismia aórtico-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Cirugía/Qx Aneurismia aórtico-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Aneurismia aorta abdominal\\NAAA","guid":"tIn6Q5Hbnw9wnNfCByCUsQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Resumen ","guid":"5CO6q97l3DUwdCw0d7IEpQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Definición:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• AAA → dilatación patológica permanente de la aorta (>1.5x\\Ndiámetro AP esperado según sexo y tamaño corporal) (1)(2)(3).","guid":"i5Ir4gjPLYMUXZxyx0xGuA","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• Umbral común: diámetro ≥3 cm (3)(4).","guid":"DKGDlmG6MqRlB4CXpIqr1A","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"•  90% de los AAA → origen infrarrenal (5).","guid":"Bg2ZDisCblIDDH5Gl2ATMg","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"Clínica:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"• AAA roto: dolor abd/lumbar nuevo, colapso CV, pérdida de conciencia.","guid":"0L-le9rhLUgRKDgSKGrD2w","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"• AAA no roto (usualmente asintomático): detectado incidental o por cribado.\\NEn casos sintomáticos: dolor abd, lumbar, inguinal.","guid":"Psq0kfvcHR0cNTI5HfA6sw","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"Factores de Riesgo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"• Tabaquismo, historia hereditaria, ⬆edad, sexo masculino (prevalencia) y femenino\\N(ruptura), trastornos congénitos/tejido conectivo, dislipidemia, EPOC, aterosclerosis, HTA,\\Nobesidad central, etnia europea, fluoroquinolonas, aneurismas en otras localizaciones.","guid":"GoriaUkLg3mbFhdYm72ZVQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"1","text":"Examen Físico:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"• Masa abd pulsátil palpable.","guid":"zuGSZs-0fXfvTedH5dh2JA","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"• Otros signos: dolor abd/flanco/lumbar, hipotensión, palidez, distensión abd, fiebre.","guid":"OUWyMs-CjjVIs-t0ucS4TQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"14","parent":"1","text":"Dx por Imágenes:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"• AAA roto: ecografía aórtica bedside o angio-TC (urgente).","guid":"pKNv5KwhHFI6dqjP6jvoJQ","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"14","text":"• AAA no roto: ecografía inicial; angio-TC/MRA para mapeo anatómico y planificación quirúrgica.","guid":"a-zwxRAN9vUPQfkovpscrA","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"1","text":"Investigaciones Dx:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"1. Ecografía aórtica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"2. A considerar: hemocultivos, examen de coagulación, VHS/CRP, hemograma, angio-TC, MRA/RM, PET-CT.","guid":"0UfDvSYv7XeEACiVTSbK1A","children":[]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"1","text":"Algoritmo Terapéutico:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"1. AAA Roto:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"• ➔ Reparación Qx urgente + medidas de resucitación.","guid":"EEFt6OPUj2Ue5rCJ70vupQ","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"21","text":"• ➔ ATB perioperatoria, analgesia, profilaxis TEV.","guid":"3HjlGK4P877Wl588foo6LQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"20","text":"2. AAA Sintomático\\Nno roto:","guid":"1dgXb4P6QGSV9jxvFQCV5Q","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"• ➔ Reparación Qx urgente + ATB perioperatoria.","guid":"0DOxRNzmm_ll3uomOdAHlw","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"• ➔ Analgesia, profilaxis TEV.","guid":"UB_1C0H10o-FozU4BDemxw","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"20","text":"3. AAA Asintomático Incidental\\N(no sintomático):","guid":"OPxF4jOnPMnxmfvWqjzOow","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"• <5.5 cm (o >4.0 cm y rápido crecimiento): vigilancia + manejo agresivo de FR CV.","guid":"ygGVfg9eRrKbK5kBBIqaDw","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"27","text":"• ≥5.5 cm (o >4.0 cm y rápido crecimiento): reparación Qx electiva + reducción\\Nde riesgo CV pr